Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithms for processing massive data sets, which is a common theme in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of straight-line programs (SLP) and Lempel-Ziv compression suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves information theory, as it deals with compressed strings, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The problem of computing the longest common subsequence is related to computational geometry, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the use of algorithms for subsequence recognition suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
